content:
Create and Configure a Queue

Queues allow groups of users to manage a shared workload more effectively. A queue is a location where records can be routed to await processing by a group member.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience in Professional, Enterprise, and Unlimited Editions that have the Financial Services Cloud enabled
To create or change queues: Customize Application AND Manage Public List Views
To change queues created by other users: Customize Application AND Manage Public List Views AND Manage Users

From Setup, enter Queues and click Queues. Click New.
Enter a label for the queue (e.g., Onboarding Queue). Add an email for the queue if necessary. Select Send Emails to Members if necessary.

Under Supported Objects, select objects to be supported by the queue (e.g., Applicant, Application Form, Party Profile).
To move objects to the Selected Objects list, click Add.
Under Queue Members, select user roles to whom you want to assign the queue (e.g., User: Agents).
To move selected members to the Selected Members list, click Add.

Assign the Interactive Steps in the Flows for Onboarding to a Queue
When the active screen flow associated with the interactive step runs, a record is assigned to the queue.
title: Creating and Configuring Queues in Financial Services Cloud
